1
00:02:18,185 --> 00:02:19,709
It all started one day...

2
00:02:19,887 --> 00:02:22,014
...after Tom heard about
Becky Thatcher...

3
00:02:22,189 --> 00:02:25,158
...going down to see 
Saint Louis with the judge.

4
00:02:25,593 --> 00:02:30,553
It just worked on him thinking
about her down there having fun.

5
00:02:30,898 --> 00:02:34,834
Time is slipping away,
and I'm getting older and older, Huck.

6
00:02:35,069 --> 00:02:39,165
There's no wars breaking out,
no continents to explore.

7
00:02:39,340 --> 00:02:42,104
No way a man can make
a name for hisself.

8
00:02:43,143 --> 00:02:46,476
And now Becky exploring.
What an outrage.

9
00:02:46,647 --> 00:02:50,014
I heard tell the Saint Louis 
papers been talking about...

10
00:02:50,184 --> 00:02:51,811
...some kind of balloon up there.

11
00:02:51,986 --> 00:02:53,977
Suppose Becky will see it.

12
00:02:54,154 --> 00:02:56,349
But probably not.

13
00:03:01,362 --> 00:03:02,920
-That's it.
-What?

14
00:03:03,097 --> 00:03:06,191
All the continents and stuff been
discovered by Christopher Columbus.

15
00:03:06,367 --> 00:03:09,461
But for certain sure,
nobody has charted the skies.

16
00:03:09,637 --> 00:03:11,696
What the sam hill are you
carrying on about?

17
00:03:11,872 --> 00:03:14,272
The balloon in the papers
near Saint Louis.

18
00:03:14,441 --> 00:03:15,430
What about it?

19
00:03:15,609 --> 00:03:19,545
You couldn't see an adventure
hanging from the end of your nose.

20
00:03:19,713 --> 00:03:22,147
Full steam ahead.

21
00:03:29,056 --> 00:03:32,492
Get your paper right here.
Halley's comet coming.

22
00:03:32,660 --> 00:03:34,890
Extra. Extra.

23
00:03:36,063 --> 00:03:39,430
The countryside was humming
because of the balloon...

24
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:42,626
...and folks said there was 
a comet heading our way.

25
00:03:44,438 --> 00:03:45,769
Penny a paper. Penny a paper.

26
00:03:47,541 --> 00:03:49,805
--like even these ones.
He might let me at least...

27
00:03:49,977 --> 00:03:52,207
...you know,
get on and walk around....

28
00:03:53,614 --> 00:03:56,515
-It's taken me a long time.
-Doomed!

29
00:03:58,352 --> 00:04:03,187
But once lost,
I could not find it with a dog.

30
00:04:05,826 --> 00:04:09,990
-Great guns.
-Amazing.

31
00:04:10,164 --> 00:04:12,928
Surely, Mr. Twain,
you aren't fool enough...

32
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:16,092
...to actually travel
in that fantastic contraption.

33
00:04:16,270 --> 00:04:20,070
The man with a new idea is a fool...

34
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:23,300
...until the idea succeeds.

35
00:04:23,477 --> 00:04:27,675
Why, Tom Sawyer and Huck Finn,
whatever are you doing here?

36
00:04:27,848 --> 00:04:29,509
-Nothing.
-Why, Becky Thatcher...

37
00:04:29,683 --> 00:04:31,810
...land sakes, what a coincidence...

38
00:04:31,985 --> 00:04:35,079
...you being here the same time
as Huck and me.

39
00:04:38,092 --> 00:04:40,287
Isn't he grand?

40
00:04:40,461 --> 00:04:43,430
I got up close so I could see,
and he stopped.

41
00:04:43,597 --> 00:04:45,258
He let me shake his hand.

42
00:04:45,432 --> 00:04:47,366
-You shook his--?
-Well, that's nothing.

43
00:04:47,534 --> 00:04:52,028
He's invited us to be the first 
inspectors of his balloon.

44
00:04:52,206 --> 00:04:54,333
-He has?
-Is that just more of your hot air?

45
00:04:54,508 --> 00:04:57,306
Come, step lively, Huck.
We'd best be getting aboard.

46
00:04:58,045 --> 00:05:00,343
So long, Becky.

47
00:05:01,048 --> 00:05:02,743
Tom....

48
00:05:03,784 --> 00:05:07,220
Where you really going
in that thing, Mr. Twain?

49
00:05:07,387 --> 00:05:09,514
Going traveling?

50
00:05:09,690 --> 00:05:12,955
Travel has no longer
any charm for me.

51
00:05:13,127 --> 00:05:16,290
I've seen all the foreign 
countries I care to see...

52
00:05:16,463 --> 00:05:18,693
...except for heaven and hell...

53
00:05:18,866 --> 00:05:25,135
...and I have only a vague curiosity
as concerns one of those.

54
00:05:25,472 --> 00:05:30,034
No, friends,
I go to meet the comet.

55
00:05:30,210 --> 00:05:32,144
He's not really gonna do that.

56
00:05:32,312 --> 00:05:36,840
-Yes indeed, I surely plan to.
-But that's dangerous.

57
00:05:37,017 --> 00:05:39,178
Come on, Huck.
Come on, hurry up.

58
00:05:39,353 --> 00:05:42,186
You're nothing but a liar
and a stowaway, Tom Sawyer.

59
00:05:42,356 --> 00:05:43,846
You too, Huck Finn.

60
00:05:44,792 --> 00:05:46,692
You mustn't.

61
00:05:48,428 --> 00:05:52,831
I came in with 
Halley's comet in 1835...

62
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,058
...when I was born.

63
00:05:54,234 --> 00:05:58,694
And I expect to go out with it.

64
00:06:03,143 --> 00:06:06,579
Oh, I'm looking forward to that.

65
00:06:17,791 --> 00:06:21,124
-Welcome to the hurricane deck.
-It stopped.

66
00:06:21,295 --> 00:06:24,423
-Whoopee, let's go.
-What in tarnation is this thing?

67
00:06:24,598 --> 00:06:26,998
Be careful, Tom.

68
00:06:28,802 --> 00:06:33,830
-Tom, where are you?
-Great Scott, what a contraption.

69
00:06:40,380 --> 00:06:42,075
-Huck.
-Look at that, Tom.

70
00:06:42,249 --> 00:06:44,240
I thought I saw someone.

71
00:06:44,418 --> 00:06:46,818
Gee willikers.

72
00:06:48,755 --> 00:06:50,245
Look at this.

73
00:06:55,596 --> 00:06:57,223
Huck.

74
00:06:58,398 --> 00:07:00,423
-Whoopee.
-Oh, no.

75
00:07:00,601 --> 00:07:03,399
-We're on our way.
-Oh, no!

76
00:07:03,570 --> 00:07:05,435
Great Scott, we gotta get off.

77
00:07:05,606 --> 00:07:07,767
Off? What's the matter with you?

78
00:07:07,941 --> 00:07:09,499
Now, I'll be celebrated.

79
00:07:09,676 --> 00:07:12,668
Tom Sawyer, the "aeronort."

80
00:07:12,913 --> 00:07:16,144
-That'll show that Becky Thatcher.
-Show her what?

81
00:07:16,316 --> 00:07:20,719
Caught you out, didn't I, Tom Sawyer?
You are stowaways.

82
00:07:20,888 --> 00:07:26,019
-Becky, you're no balloon inspector.
-Neither are you.

83
00:07:26,660 --> 00:07:30,118
Are you ever gonna catch it
when your Aunt Polly gets ahold of--

84
00:07:30,297 --> 00:07:33,027
-Welcome to the hurricane deck.
-Boys. Tom. Huck.

85
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:35,998
-Mark Twain.
-And Becky Thatcher.

86
00:07:36,169 --> 00:07:39,764
-How did he know our names?
-Hello, my angelfish.

87
00:07:39,940 --> 00:07:44,707
More every day you remind me
of my wife, Livy, God rest her.

88
00:07:45,212 --> 00:07:49,012
Same combination
of innocence and sand.

89
00:07:49,182 --> 00:07:52,515
Same carefree laugh of a girl.

90
00:07:52,686 --> 00:07:55,883
What happened to Livy,
Mr. Twain?

91
00:07:56,189 --> 00:07:58,020
To the helm.
We've work to do.

92
00:08:00,761 --> 00:08:03,355
Mr. Twain, there's been
some kind of an accident.

93
00:08:03,530 --> 00:08:06,260
I think a miscalculation.

94
00:08:06,433 --> 00:08:10,494
-Not by a considerable sight.
-But we're taking off.

95
00:08:10,671 --> 00:08:12,536
What a view.

96
00:08:12,806 --> 00:08:15,900
-How are we gonna get down?
-You keep a tight tongue, Huck.

97
00:08:16,076 --> 00:08:19,705
-This is bully up here, Mr. Twain.
-This is glorious.

98
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:21,643
-Did we ever strike it lucky.
-Yeah.

99
00:08:21,815 --> 00:08:24,841
-How high are we?
-How are we gonna get back down?

100
00:08:25,018 --> 00:08:30,388
-Down is not our destination, my boy.
-Oh, no.

101
00:08:30,557 --> 00:08:31,956
You mean we're--?

102
00:08:32,125 --> 00:08:35,652
-Where are we going?
-To Halley's comet.

103
00:08:35,829 --> 00:08:37,057
Halley's comet?

104
00:08:37,497 --> 00:08:40,762
-We'd get--
-Burned to a crisp.

105
00:08:41,101 --> 00:08:43,797
It will be the greatest
disappointment of my life...

106
00:08:43,971 --> 00:08:47,065
...if I don't meet up with that comet.

107
00:08:49,242 --> 00:08:52,541
-Have a look back here.
-The man's plumb crazy.

108
00:08:52,713 --> 00:08:56,615
-I wanna show you something.
-Well, I'm not. You stick with me.

109
00:08:57,784 --> 00:09:00,082
See here.
Now, we cross the Atlantic...

110
00:09:00,253 --> 00:09:01,811
...catch this trade wind...

111
00:09:01,989 --> 00:09:05,447
...to where the comet's parabola
comes close to the Earth.

112
00:09:05,625 --> 00:09:07,092
Or close enough.

113
00:09:07,961 --> 00:09:11,453
How come a writer knows so much
about piloting and navigating?

114
00:09:11,631 --> 00:09:16,591
Because long before I was a writer,
I was a Mississippi riverboat pilot.

115
00:09:18,772 --> 00:09:22,230
Say, that's an uncommon fine frog.

116
00:09:22,409 --> 00:09:23,467
Well, that's Homer.

117
00:09:23,643 --> 00:09:28,740
You know, it was a frog like Homer
that put me in the writing business.

118
00:09:29,583 --> 00:09:35,886
I wrote a story about The Celebrated
Jumping Frog of Calaveras County.

119
00:09:36,056 --> 00:09:37,683
That's right here.

120
00:09:37,858 --> 00:09:40,292
Home of Jim Smiley and
his famous frog, Dan'l Webster.

121
00:09:41,895 --> 00:09:43,260
Famous frog?

122
00:09:43,430 --> 00:09:46,661
Will you tell me what in tarnation
a frog could do to get hisself famous?

123
00:09:46,833 --> 00:09:47,822
Oh, Tom.

124
00:09:48,001 --> 00:09:51,459
I've been trying everything I know,
and I ain't even a little bit famous yet.

125
00:09:51,638 --> 00:09:53,629
Well, I'll tell you all about him.

126
00:09:53,807 --> 00:09:56,173
Just as it was told to me.

127
00:09:58,712 --> 00:10:00,805
What a fellow, that Jim Smiley.

128
00:10:00,981 --> 00:10:04,473
Always betting on anything
that turned up.

129
00:10:04,651 --> 00:10:09,088
Only thing is,
he made sure he won every bet.

130
00:10:11,591 --> 00:10:14,355
He catched a frog one day
and took him home...

131
00:10:14,528 --> 00:10:17,588
...and said he'd calculate
to educate him.

132
00:10:17,964 --> 00:10:21,092
All a frog wants is educating...

133
00:10:21,268 --> 00:10:24,635
...and he can do most anything.

134
00:10:25,372 --> 00:10:27,567
And so he never done nothing
for three months...

135
00:10:27,741 --> 00:10:30,767
...but sat in his back yard
and learned that frog to jump.

136
00:10:30,944 --> 00:10:32,673
And you bet he did learn him too.

137
00:10:32,846 --> 00:10:38,284
All right, Dan'l, let's 
just see how far you can go.

138
00:10:43,557 --> 00:10:48,221
Come on back now.
One for accuracy.

139
00:10:54,434 --> 00:10:58,962
Smiley knew a sucker
when he saw one.

140
00:11:04,444 --> 00:11:06,776
What might that be
you got in the barrel?

141
00:11:06,947 --> 00:11:08,881
Well, it might be a parrot.

142
00:11:09,049 --> 00:11:11,176
Might be a canary, maybe.

143
00:11:11,351 --> 00:11:13,046
But it ain't.

144
00:11:14,087 --> 00:11:16,419
It's only just a frog.

145
00:11:19,426 --> 00:11:21,451
So it is.

146
00:11:21,995 --> 00:11:23,895
What's he good for?

147
00:11:24,064 --> 00:11:27,033
Well, he's good enough
for one thing I should judge.

148
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:31,193
He can out-jump any frog
in Calaveras County.

149
00:11:34,741 --> 00:11:38,609
Well, I don't see no points
about that frog...

150
00:11:38,778 --> 00:11:41,406
...that's any better
than any other frog.

151
00:11:41,581 --> 00:11:45,779
Maybe you just don't
understand frogs.

152
00:11:45,952 --> 00:11:48,614
Anyway, I got my opinion...

153
00:11:48,788 --> 00:11:50,779
...and I'll just rest 40 dollars...

154
00:11:50,957 --> 00:11:55,792
...that he can out-jump 
any frog in Calaveras County.

155
00:11:56,463 --> 00:12:00,297
Well, I'm only a stranger here.

156
00:12:00,934 --> 00:12:03,494
I ain't got no frog.

157
00:12:04,204 --> 00:12:06,536
But if I had a frog, I'd bet you.

158
00:12:06,706 --> 00:12:11,040
That's all right.
I'll go get you a frog.

159
00:12:16,116 --> 00:12:18,744
You hungry, frog?

160
00:12:24,291 --> 00:12:26,282
Smiley went to the swamp...

161
00:12:26,459 --> 00:12:30,828
...and slopped around 
in the mud for a long time.

162
00:12:39,272 --> 00:12:40,899
Finally, he fetched a frog...

163
00:12:41,074 --> 00:12:43,201
...and fetched him in
to give him to this fellow.

164
00:12:43,376 --> 00:12:46,072
Eurekee!

165
00:12:47,647 --> 00:12:51,310
-Here he comes.
-There's your frog.

166
00:12:51,484 --> 00:12:54,044
The likes of that....

167
00:12:57,090 --> 00:13:00,685
Putting my money on Smiley's frog.

168
00:13:00,860 --> 00:13:03,260
-Me too.
-Count me in.

169
00:13:03,463 --> 00:13:07,832
Now then, if you're ready,
set him alongside of Dan'l...

170
00:13:08,001 --> 00:13:10,265
...with his forepaws even
with Dan'l's...

171
00:13:10,437 --> 00:13:12,200
...and I'll give the word.

172
00:13:13,373 --> 00:13:15,671
On your marks, get set...

173
00:13:15,842 --> 00:13:16,934
...get!

174
00:13:17,110 --> 00:13:20,978
Come on, jump.
Get in there, boy, would you?

175
00:13:21,147 --> 00:13:24,947
What's the matter with you?
Will you start jumping?

176
00:13:28,221 --> 00:13:29,950
I said, get.

177
00:13:35,662 --> 00:13:38,893
Get off that starting line.
Get going.

178
00:13:41,334 --> 00:13:43,802
-Get off of that--
-Jump there. Come on now.

179
00:13:54,347 --> 00:13:57,475
-Oh, no.
-Will you just jump?

180
00:13:57,651 --> 00:14:00,848
Jump. Jump, frog. Get going.

181
00:14:06,726 --> 00:14:09,217
-We won, frog.
-What do you mean, you won?

182
00:14:09,396 --> 00:14:13,492
Dag blame it, Smiley.
That was the last 40 dollars I had.

183
00:14:19,105 --> 00:14:22,336
Well, as I said before...

184
00:14:22,642 --> 00:14:27,602
...I don't see no points about that frog
that's any better than any other frog.

185
00:14:27,781 --> 00:14:29,112
I do wonder...

186
00:14:29,282 --> 00:14:33,218
...why in tarnation
that there frog just give up.

187
00:14:33,386 --> 00:14:35,946
Wonder if there ain't something
the matter with him.

188
00:14:36,122 --> 00:14:39,819
Appears to look 
mighty baggy somehow.

189
00:14:41,661 --> 00:14:43,891
Why, blame my cats...

190
00:14:44,064 --> 00:14:47,056
...if he don't weigh 50 pounds!

191
00:14:49,102 --> 00:14:51,593
I've been hornswoggled!

192
00:14:51,771 --> 00:14:53,739
He was the maddest man.

193
00:14:53,907 --> 00:14:58,105
He took out after that fella,
but he never catched him.

194
00:15:03,883 --> 00:15:06,147
Shucks, I could write a better
story than that one.

195
00:15:06,319 --> 00:15:07,308
Tom!

196
00:15:07,487 --> 00:15:10,115
That's what I said myself
when I heard it.

197
00:15:10,290 --> 00:15:13,088
It was a big success all the same.

198
00:15:13,259 --> 00:15:15,386
I became a writer.

199
00:15:15,562 --> 00:15:18,292
I haven't worked a day since.

200
00:15:19,265 --> 00:15:23,964
-Now, that's a job I'd like to get.
-If you get out of here alive.

201
00:15:33,780 --> 00:15:36,271
There she is.

202
00:15:37,851 --> 00:15:41,014
How come you wanna catch
that comet so bad, Mr. Twain?

203
00:15:41,988 --> 00:15:46,687
The comet and I are a part 
of the plan, angelfish.

204
00:15:46,860 --> 00:15:48,953
No doubt the Almighty 
has said here:

205
00:15:49,129 --> 00:15:51,689
"Here goes those
two unaccountable freaks.

206
00:15:51,865 --> 00:15:57,132
They came in together,
they must go out together."

207
00:15:58,538 --> 00:16:03,237
Here, set your eyes
on this celestial schooner.

208
00:16:08,047 --> 00:16:10,914
Now ain't that
a heartwarming spectacle.

209
00:16:11,084 --> 00:16:12,813
It's beauti--

210
00:16:13,686 --> 00:16:18,680
Well, Tom and Huck and I,
well, see, we're not so sure--

211
00:16:18,858 --> 00:16:22,794
That I know what I'm doing up here?

212
00:16:23,463 --> 00:16:27,058
Angelfish,
It's just like piloting a river.

213
00:16:27,233 --> 00:16:29,565
You get to know the shape of it.

214
00:16:29,836 --> 00:16:34,136
Like following a hall
at home in the dark.

215
00:16:34,307 --> 00:16:39,142
And even if you feel some fear,
you know no harm can come to you...

216
00:16:39,312 --> 00:16:42,611
...because you've traveled
that hallway a hundred times...

217
00:16:42,782 --> 00:16:46,775
...in nothing but bare feet and faith.

218
00:17:00,099 --> 00:17:01,760
What are we gonna do?

219
00:17:01,935 --> 00:17:03,232
You know your ownself...

220
00:17:03,403 --> 00:17:06,236
...we gotta find a way off
of this here balloon, Tom Sawyer.

221
00:17:06,406 --> 00:17:08,499
Adventure or no.

222
00:17:08,675 --> 00:17:13,112
Okay now, Homer, over here.
Now over there.

223
00:17:13,513 --> 00:17:15,140
Well?

224
00:17:15,949 --> 00:17:19,612
I got a plan
just starting to brew.

225
00:17:19,786 --> 00:17:21,117
Well, what is it?

226
00:17:21,287 --> 00:17:24,723
First, we gotta get Becky off.
She talks too much.

227
00:17:24,891 --> 00:17:26,381
Can't keep a secret.

228
00:17:26,559 --> 00:17:27,958
So me and Huck was thinking...

229
00:17:28,127 --> 00:17:30,561
...we should set her down
and let Becky off.

230
00:17:30,730 --> 00:17:32,789
Things are liable to get pretty rough.

231
00:17:32,966 --> 00:17:36,595
There is nothing comparable
to the endurance of a woman.

232
00:17:36,769 --> 00:17:38,327
But this is different, Mr. Twain.

233
00:17:38,505 --> 00:17:40,370
We're aeronorts,
and girls don't belong--

234
00:17:40,540 --> 00:17:42,940
That's "aeronauts."

235
00:17:45,879 --> 00:17:49,679
She would have to horn in
on this expedition.

236
00:17:53,253 --> 00:17:55,244
-To the main deck.
-There's that thing again.

237
00:17:55,421 --> 00:17:57,912
Come on, let's go investigating.

238
00:17:59,692 --> 00:18:03,560
-Tom, where you going?
-This thing's really amazing.

239
00:18:03,730 --> 00:18:06,198
Gives me the creeps.

240
